wiki.content: “Angel Of My Dreams” is the debut solo single by JADE, former Little Mix member. On June 27, she announced that her debut single was coming and on July 2nd, she officially announced the song for July 19 along with a snippet of it. JADE co-wrote 'Angel of My Dreams' in LA alongside Steph Jones, who worked on Sabrina Carpenter's 'Espresso', Pablo Bowman and producer Mike Sabbath who's has worked previously with Meghan Trainor, Raye and Little Mix. On 19 July 2024, she released "Angel of My Dreams" as her debut solo single and the lead to her upcoming debut solo album. It received widespread acclaim from critics with praise given towards the track lyrics, use of sample, and exploration of different genres. It debuted and peaked at #7 on the UK Singles Charts, becoming the third Little Mix-alumna to score a solo Top 10-hit. It went on to become the only Little Mix-solo single to spend more than one week in the Top 10 and the Little Mix-solo single with the most weeks in the UK Top 40. Read more on Last.fm.
